      "content": "i get that, but i'm worried. if the abstract says \"N=10\" the reviewers might just trash it before they even read the findings. \n\ncould we maybe word it more broadly? like, instead of \"ten participants,\" maybe say \"a targeted cohort of experts\" or just \"a representative sample\"? we aren't really lying, we're just framing it so the impact isn't lost in the numbers. what do you think?",
